= section "The Subjunctive Mood" do
  %p Formal and literary registers of Tunisian have three tenses in the subjunctive mood: an analytic present subjunctive, and periphrastic past and future subjunctives. The past subjunctive consists of the present subjunctive of <i>ystâ</i> or <i>ebê</i> plus a participle (just like the perfect tense), while the future subjunctive consists of a special auxiliary verb, an article, and an infinitive (just like the Future II). The subjunctive is mostly absent in colloquial usage.

